'''''Managers of Virtue: Public School Leadership in America, 1820–1980''''' is a history book by [[David Tyack]] and Elisabeth Hansot. Its first two sections discuss American educational leadership in the [[common school]] and [[Progressive era]]s, and its last part discusses the subsequent decline in school leader authority and public confidence.

